Tell HN: Outlook webmail on Android requires Chrome or Edge, not Firefox
text:
One of my employers used o365 with fairly draconian rules. Trying to log in with my free browser of choice yields the lovely, monopolist message:

>You can't get there from here You cannot access the resource from this browser on your device. You need to use Chrome or Edge.

> Error Code: 530001 >App name: Office 365 Exchange Online App ID: 00000002-0000-0ff1-ce00-000000000000

Why? It's a static website in accessibility mode. What reason could be behind this? Didn't the EU literally fine Microsoft for exactly this sort of behaviour?

Ask HN: Does Symantic Search Work?
text:
Looking through HN posts over the last 30 days there are at least 15 posts for symantic search. I'm excited about the prospect but haven't seen good results.

Is there any info on query performance? And to builders, did you get better results by incorporating semantic search?
